parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of seat belts to retract or restrain occupants can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash, compromising vehicle safety.
symptoms: The seat belts do not fully retract
the seat belts get caught in the door when exiting the vehicle
the seat belts do not restrain occupants in a crash
the seat belts do not lock in the holders.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The recurring failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to slip or hesitate while shifting gears, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents. Additionally, frequent clutch replacements can lead to increased maintenance costs and downtime.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates while shifting gears
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive rust and corrosion of the frame can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to a loss of safety and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Visible rust and corrosion on the frame
weakened frame structure
vehicle no longer safe to drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake caliper can cause a loss of braking power, leading to increased stopping distances and a higher risk of accidents.
symptoms: Spongy brake pedal
uneven brake wear
grinding or screeching noise when applying the brakes
brake warning light on the dashboard
difficulty stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The parking brake malfunction can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, even when the parking brake is engaged, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The parking brake does not release properly
the parking brake sticks
the parking brake pedal feels stiff or hard to push
the vehicle rolls or moves when the parking brake is engaged
the parking brake warning light is illuminated on the dashboard.
